ratings.rComments: Easy A indeed. His lectures are sort of boring though.

Pretty easy class overall. There's reading every week (super boring) and weekly reading assignments which are easy enough if you skim the reading. Lectures are crazy boring, but you should show up just so that you're not cramming last minute before the exams. 2 midterms, no final. 1 book report and some in-class exercises. Easy A.

Manalansan was very understanding and approachable during the online course I took. I missed a quiz the first week because I hadn't expected one due the first Wednesday, and I emailed him and he extended the due date. His tests and assignments were very reasonable and manageable. He is flexible and offers plenty of extra credit.
Martin is awesome and the class is super easy. Show up, take notes and you are guaranteed to get the easiest A. I enjoyed his class so much that I w=am considering taking him for future courses.
